**Primitive-first rule:** Every component that CAN be composed from `Box`, `Text`, `Icon` MUST be. Exceptions: Gluestack overlay compounds (Tooltip) manage DOM portals; HTML input wrappers (DatePicker, ColorPicker, etc.) wrap native elements for semantic/accessibility reasons. Form inputs (Checkbox, Radio, Select, Slider, Textarea) are kept for their native behavior and accessibility semantics.

**Rule:** When adding a new palette entry, prefer `Box`/`Text`/`Icon` primitives. Use Gluestack compound components only when no primitive equivalent exists. All new Gluestack compound sub-components need `REQUIRED_PARENT` / `ALLOWED_CHILDREN` entries in `_store.ts`.

