## Critical Bug Fixes (Do Not Repeat)

### 1. Button disappears when any className is added

**Root cause:** `components/ui/button/index.tsx` used `hasCustomClassName(className)` ŌĆö any non-empty className (even `py-0 px-0` from padding) triggered `effectiveAction = 'custom'` ŌåÆ `bg-transparent`.

**Fix:** Only switch to `'custom'` action when className contains a `bg-*` token:
```tsx
const hasBg = useCustom && /\bbg-/.test(className!);
const effectiveAction = hasBg ? 'custom' : action;
```
**Rule:** Adding padding, margin, border-radius, opacity, or any non-color class to a Button must NOT override its background color.

---

### 2. Opacity uses inline `style.opacity`, never `opacity-N` class

**Root cause:** NativeWind does not compile dynamically applied `opacity-95`, `opacity-50` etc. (they're not in the source at build time).

**Fix:** Store opacity as `style.opacity` (decimal 0ŌĆō1). The slider `min=5` prevents accidental 0%. At 100%, `style.opacity` is removed entirely.

**Rule:** Never add `opacity-N` classes dynamically. Always use `patchStyle({ opacity: String(val/100) })`.

---

### 3. Rotation uses inline `style.transform`, never `rotate-[Ndeg]` class

**Root cause:** Same NativeWind dynamic class compilation issue.

**Fix:** Store rotation as `style.transform = rotate(Ndeg)`.

**Rule:** Never add `rotate-[...]` classes dynamically. Use `patchStyle({ transform: \`rotate(\${deg}deg)\` })`.

---

### 3b. Overlay ring / X/Y/W/H lag during panel edits (rotation, opacity, etc.)

**Root cause 1 (ring lag):** The overlay's `useLayoutEffect` and `selectedRects` useMemo depended only on `tick` (RAF loop). The RAF loop stops 200 ms after the last canvas hover/scroll. When the user is only clicking the panel, `tick` is frozen ŌåÆ ring doesn't reposition to match the newly rotated element.

**Fix:** Added `pageNodes` to both `useLayoutEffect([tick, pageNodes])` and `selectedRects` useMemo deps in `_overlay.tsx`. Every `patchProp` call creates a new `pageNodes` reference, triggering the layout effect before paint.

**Root cause 2 (X/Y/W/H lag):** `domMetrics` was a `useMemo` that ran during the render phase (before React committed the new style to DOM). It read stale BCR values. Also, `patchStyle` debounces the Zustand commit by 80 ms, so during rapid pressing the `useLayoutEffect([store.pageNodes])` that recomputes domMetrics fires at most once per 80 ms.

**Fix 1:** Converted `domMetrics` from `useMemo` to `useState` driven by `useLayoutEffect` (after commit ŌåÆ correct BCR).

**Fix 2:** Inside `patchStyle`, right after the direct DOM mutation (step 1), read `getBoundingClientRect()` and imperatively set `.value` on the `input-pos-x/y/w/h` DOM inputs. This gives frame-perfect X/Y/W/H updates with zero React re-renders ŌĆö same frame as the component rotation.

**Rule:** Any panel control that produces a direct DOM mutation via `patchStyle` step 1 must also update any read-only DOM metrics displays imperatively (via `querySelector + inp.value = ...`) in the same synchronous call, NOT via React state. React state (domMetrics) is the fallback for zoom changes, node selection changes, and the post-debounce settle render.

---

### 4. Colors use inline `style.backgroundColor / color / borderColor`

**Root cause:** NativeWind doesn't reliably compile arbitrary `bg-[#hex]` classes set dynamically at runtime.

**Fix:** All color picker changes use `patchStyle({ backgroundColor: hex })`, `patchStyle({ color: hex })`, `patchStyle({ borderColor: hex })`.

---

### 5. Flip H/V toggle-off didn't work (`\b` regex bug)

**Root cause:** `removeTwToken(cls, '-scale-x-')` generated regex `\b-scale-x-\S*`. The `\b` (word boundary) never fires before `-` (non-word char), so `-scale-x-100` could never be removed.

**Fix:** `removeTwToken` detects when prefix starts with a non-word char and uses `(?:^|\s)` boundary instead:
```ts
if (/^\w/.test(prefix)) {
  return className.replace(new RegExp(`\\b${escaped}\\S*`, 'g'), '')...
}
return className.replace(new RegExp(`(?:^|\\s)${escaped}\\S*`, 'g'), ' ')...
```
**Rule:** Any Tailwind utility starting with `-` (negated scale, negated rotate) requires the `(?:^|\s)` boundary, not `\b`.

---

### 6. Border radius: per-corner arbitrary-px tokens

**Current design:** Each corner (TL, TR, BR, BL) has an independent `NumberInput` in the panel. Entering a pixel value writes `rounded-{corner}-[Xpx]` via `patchStyle({borderTopLeftRadius: 'Xpx'})` ŌåÆ `styleToClassName`. There is no global rollup (even when all 4 corners are equal, 4 per-corner classes are written).

**Reading:** `expandBorderRadius` reads the current className and returns a per-corner pixel map `{tl, tr, br, bl}`. It resolves:
1. Explicit per-corner arbitrary class (`rounded-tl-[8px]` ŌåÆ 8)
2. Fallback to global arbitrary class (`rounded-[8px]` ŌåÆ 8 for all corners)
3. Scale token backward-compat (`rounded-lg` ŌåÆ 8, `rounded-full` ŌåÆ 9999)

**Writing:** `patchStyle({borderTopLeftRadius: 'Npx'})` ŌåÆ `styleToClassName` emits `rounded-tl-[Npx]` and strips all existing radius tokens for that corner.

**Rule:** All new border-radius writes must use `patchStyle` with explicit `px` values. Never emit bare scale tokens like `rounded-lg` or `rounded-full` ŌĆö always use `rounded-[Xpx]` / `rounded-tl-[Xpx]`.

**Animated nodes ŌĆö border-radius on outer wrapper:**
For nodes that have an `animation` config (enter, hover, loop, etc.), `AnimatedNode` wraps the content in an outer `View`/`Animated.View` that holds `data-builder-id`. In builder mode, `renderer.tsx` automatically forwards `rounded-[Xpx]` / `rounded-{corner}-[Xpx]` from the inner node's `className` to the outer wrapper's `outerStyle`. This ensures:
1. `patchStyle({ borderRadius })` on the `data-builder-id` element produces a visible effect
2. The selection ring in `_overlay.tsx` reads the outer wrapper's border-radius (via `el.style.borderRadius` or `getComputedStyle`) and applies it to the ring, so the ring follows rounded corners

**Safelist:** `tailwind.config.js` includes `{ pattern: /^rounded-\[\d+px\]$/ }` and `{ pattern: /^rounded-(tl|tr|br|bl)-\[\d+px\]$/ }` so that AI-generated arbitrary-px border-radius classes always have compiled CSS, even if they don't appear in static build-time content files.

---

### 7. CONTAINER_TYPES Must Stay in Sync Across Three Files

**Root cause:** `CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_canvas.tsx` and `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_panel-left.tsx` only contained a few types. Any type NOT in this set is treated as a leaf ŌĆö you cannot drop children into it when it's empty (the `children.length > 0` fallback only helps non-empty containers).

**Impact:** `Center`, `Grid`, `GridItem`, and all Gluestack compound containers were non-droppable when first placed on the canvas.

**Fix:** All three sets must include the **same container types**:
- `_canvas.tsx` ŌåÆ `CONTAINER_TYPES` (controls drag-over hit logic)
- `_panel-left.tsx` ŌåÆ `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` (controls layers-panel expand icon)
- `_panel-right.tsx` ŌåÆ `isContainer` array (controls Auto Layout design panel section)

**Rule:** Whenever you add a new container component to the palette, add its `type` string to all three locations. The canonical list is in `_panel-right.tsx`'s `isContainer` array.

---

### 8. defaultNode className Must Include All Implicit Style Tokens

**Root cause:** The right panel reads layout/alignment tokens (`flex-row`, `flex-col`, `items-*`, `justify-*`) exclusively from `props.className`. Gluestack compound components (Center, VStack, HStack, etc.) apply these tokens internally via their `tva` base styles ŌĆö NOT from `props.className`. So when a component is freshly dropped, the panel shows no direction selected and no alignment cell highlighted even though the component visually centers/stacks correctly.

**Fix:** Always include all layout-defining tokens explicitly in `defaultNode.props.className`:
- `Center` ŌåÆ `flex flex-col items-center justify-center`
- `VStack` ŌåÆ `flex flex-col`
- `HStack` ŌåÆ `flex flex-row`
- Any other container with an implicit flex direction or alignment ŌåÆ add those tokens to `className`

**Rule:** If a component has implicit `flex-*`, `items-*`, or `justify-*` built into its component style, mirror those tokens in `defaultNode.className` so the right panel reflects the actual visual behavior immediately on drop.

---

### 9. Padding / Margin / Gap ŌĆö exact pixel values via inline style

**Root cause:** Using Tailwind spacing scale (`pxToSpacingScale`) forced values to snap to 2px increments. Input `1` ŌåÆ rounded to `0` ŌåÆ no margin. Input `3` ŌåÆ `mx-0.5` (not compiled in older safelist).

**Fix:** All three use `patchStyle` with direct CSS properties:
- Padding: `style.paddingLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`
- Margin: `style.marginLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`
- Gap: `style.gap`

**Rule:** Never use `patchCls(applyPadding/applyMargin/pxToTw)` for user-entered spacing values in the builder. Use `patchStyle` with exact `px` strings so any value the user types is applied exactly.

---

### 8. Lifecycle triggers must NOT become DOM event props

**Problem:** `action-binding.ts` `bindEventHandler` has a catch-all `else` that converts any unrecognised trigger name to a camelCase prop (e.g. `created` ŌåÆ `onCreated`). React logs "Unknown event handler property `onCreated`" and silently drops it. The handler never fires.

**Triggers affected:** `created`, `mounted`, `submitValidationError` ŌĆö these are lifecycle/engine events, not DOM events.

**Fix:** Added `LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS` set in `action-binding.ts`. Early return at the top of `bindEventHandler` when `LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS.has(event)`.

```ts
const LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS = new Set(['created', 'mounted', 'submitValidationError']);
// inside bindEventHandler:
if (LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS.has(event)) return;
```

**Rule:** Any new trigger that is not a DOM event must be added to `LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS` in `action-binding.ts`.

---

### 9. `navigateTo` step must use `type:'navigate'`, not `action:'navigate'`

**Problem:** `stepToSdui` for `navigateTo` returned `{ action: 'navigate', payload: { path } }`. In `runOne`, `actionsConfig['navigate']` is `undefined` (no named action). `dispatchToHandler(undefined, ...)` throws `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'type')` ŌĆö crashing the page.

**Fix:** Changed `stepToSdui` `navigateTo` case to return `{ type: 'navigate', path, routeConfig, linkType, externalUrl, newTab }`. The `runOne` fallback (`'type' in action`) catches this and dispatches to `ACTION_HANDLERS['navigate']` correctly.

```ts
// workflow-steps-handler.ts
case 'navigateTo':
  if (cfg.queryParams) { return { type: 'navigateWithQuery', ... }; }
  return { type: 'navigate', path: cfg.path, routeConfig: cfg.routeConfig, ... };
```

Also added `if (!actionDef) return false;` guard at the top of `dispatchToHandler` in `actions/handlers/index.ts` for defensive safety.

**Rule:** `stepToSdui` must always return objects with `type:` (not `action:`). Actions keyed by name live in actionsConfig and are resolved by the outer `runOne` ŌĆö they must not be embedded as action refs inside `stepToSdui`.

---

### 8. `pxToSpacingScale` ties round UP

When a px value is equally distant between two scale values (e.g. `1` ties between `0` and `2`), round UP:
```ts
.reduce((a, b) => Math.abs(b - px) <= Math.abs(a - px) ? b : a);
```
Previously used `<` which always rounded down ŌåÆ `1` ŌåÆ `0` ŌåÆ no spacing.

---

## `_tw-utils.ts` ŌĆö Key Utilities

### `removeTwToken(className, prefix)`
Removes all tokens matching prefix. Uses `\b` for word-char prefixes (`p-`, `gap-`, `rounded-`). Uses `(?:^|\s)` for non-word-char prefixes (`-scale-x-`, `-rotate-`).

### `replaceTwToken(className, prefix, newToken)`
Replaces the first matching token, or appends if none found. Uses `(?:^|\s)` boundary with space-preserving replacement.

### `parseTwToken(className, prefix)`
Returns the first token matching `\b{prefix}\S*`, or `null`.

### `expandPadding / expandBorderRadius / expandMargin`
Parse className into structured px/token values for display in inputs. These are ONLY used for reading initial values (display). Writing always uses `patchStyle`.

### `applyAlignment(className, cellIdx)`
Maps 0ŌĆō8 cell index ŌåÆ `items-*` + `justify-*` classes. Used by the 9-cell grid.

### `globalToCornerToken(global, corner)`
Legacy helper: `'rounded-lg'` + `'tl'` ŌåÆ `'rounded-tl-lg'`. Kept for backward-compat reading of old scale-token nodes. New writes always use `rounded-{corner}-[Xpx]` via `patchStyle`.

---

## Tailwind Safelist (`tailwind.config.js`)

All dynamically applied builder classes must be in the safelist. Current coverage:
- **Spacing (arbitrary-px):** `pt/pr/pb/pl/px/py-[*]`, `mt/mr/mb/ml/mx/my-[*]`, `gap-[*]`, `gap-x-[*]`, `gap-y-[*]`
- **Dimensions (arbitrary-px):** `w-[*]`, `h-[*]`, `max-w-[*]`
- **Border radius (arbitrary-px):** `rounded-[*]`, `rounded-tl/tr/br/bl-[*]`
- **Border width (arbitrary-px):** `border-[*px]`
- **Typography (arbitrary-px):** `text-[*px]`
- **Z-index (arbitrary):** `z-[*]`
- **Scale tokens (legacy backward-compat):** `p/px/py/pt/pr/pb/pl-{scale}`, `rounded-{size}`, `text-{size}`, `border-{size}` ŌĆö kept so old nodes display correctly; new writes always use arbitrary-px
- Flex: direction, items, justify, wrap
- Rotate (including negated and arbitrary): `-?rotate-(N|[...])`, `-?scale-x/y-*`
- Position: `static/relative/absolute/fixed/sticky`
- Z-index scale: `z-0/10/20/30/40/50/auto`
- Cursor, display, overflow, text-align, text-decoration, text-transform, self-*
- Shadow: `shadow-{size}` (still scale-token based)
- Font weight: `font-{weight}` (still scale-token based)
- Opacity: `opacity-{value}` (still scale-token based)

**Rule:** Any new class dynamically applied by the builder must be added to the safelist OR stored as an inline style property. Spacing, dimensions, border-radius, border-width, and font-size are ALL written as `[Xpx]` arbitrary classes ŌĆö never as scale tokens.

