## E2E Tests

Tests use `window.__builderStore` (exposed at **module level** in `_store.ts`, NOT in a `useEffect`) to read/write Zustand state directly. Available as soon as the JS bundle loads, before React hydration completes.

**`gotoBuilder` pattern:**
```ts
async function gotoBuilder(page: Page) {
  await page.goto('/dev/builder');
  await page.waitForSelector('[data-builder-page-frame]', { timeout: 30_000 });
  await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="tab-components"]', { timeout: 15_000 });
  await page.waitForFunction(
    () => !!(window as unknown as Record<string, unknown>).__builderStore,
    { timeout: 20_000, polling: 100 }
  );
}
```

**`injectNodes` pattern** (preferred over drag-and-drop):
```ts
async function injectNodes(page: Page, nodes: unknown[]) {
  await page.evaluate((n) => {
    (window as unknown as Record<string, { getState: () => { _setPageNodes: (n: unknown[]) => void } }>)
      .__builderStore.getState()._setPageNodes(n);
  }, nodes);
  // ALL nodes must have `id` for data-builder-id to be set
  await page.waitForSelector(`[data-builder-id="${(nodes[0] as {id: string}).id}"]`, { timeout: 8_000 });
}
```

**Key helpers:**
- `gotoBuilder(page)` ŌĆö navigate to `/dev/builder`, wait for frame + tabs + store
- `injectNodes(page, nodes)` ŌĆö set page nodes directly via store (bypasses flaky drag-and-drop)
- `selectViaLayers(page)` ŌĆö click Layers tab ŌåÆ first layer-row ŌåÆ Design tab
- `getNodeClassName(page, nodeId)` ŌĆö reads `node.props.className` from store
- `getNodeStyle(page, nodeId)` ŌĆö reads `node.props.style` from store
- `scrollTo(page, testId)` ŌĆö scrolls element into view inside overflow panel container

**`sharedPage` + `resetBuilder` pattern** (mandatory for ALL spec files ŌĆö navigate once, reset between tests):

```ts
import { test, expect, Page, Browser } from '@playwright/test';

let sharedPage: Page;

async function resetBuilder(p: Page) {
  await p.evaluate(() => {
    const store = (window as unknown as Record<string, { getState: () => Record<string, unknown> }>).__builderStore?.getState();
    if (!store) return;
    (store._setPageNodes as (n: unknown[]) => void)([]);
    if (typeof store.setSelectedIds === 'function') (store.setSelectedIds as (ids: string[]) => void)([]);
    if (typeof store.setZoom === 'function') (store.setZoom as (z: number) => void)(1);
  });
  await p.waitForFunction(
    () => document.querySelectorAll('[data-builder-id]').length === 0,
    { timeout: 5_000 }
  );
}

// File-level (outside any describe) ŌĆö opens ONE page for the entire file
test.beforeAll(async ({ browser }: { browser: Browser }) => {
  sharedPage = await browser.newPage();
  await gotoBuilder(sharedPage);
});
test.afterAll(async () => { await sharedPage?.close(); });
test.beforeEach(async () => { await resetBuilder(sharedPage); }); // only if no describe-level beforeEach

// Inside a describe block ŌĆö same pattern:
test.describe('My Group', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async () => { await resetBuilder(sharedPage); });
  test('my test', async () => {
    const page = sharedPage; // alias so existing code works unchanged
    // ...
  });
});
```

**Why `resetBuilder` instead of `gotoBuilder`:** Full page navigation costs 5ŌĆō15s per test. `resetBuilder` clears nodes/selection/zoom via the store in <100ms. Always prefer `resetBuilder` in `beforeEach`; reserve `gotoBuilder` only for cases that require a fresh undo history (e.g. History/Undo tests in `builder.spec.ts`).

**History tests exception:** `_setPageNodes([])` does NOT clear the undo stack. Tests that test undo/redo must use `gotoBuilder(page)` (the Playwright fixture page, not `sharedPage`) so each gets a clean history:
```ts
test.describe('History (Undo / Redo)', () => {
  // No beforeEach here ŌĆö each test uses its own page fixture
  test('undo after drop removes the node', async ({ page }) => {
    await gotoBuilder(page); // fresh page = clean history
    // ...
  });
});
```

**Test series:**
- `BP-00`ŌĆō`BP-44` (in `panel-interactive.spec.ts`): Box-based button, all right-panel controls. Replaces old `button-panel.spec.ts` (deleted).
- `PI-01`ŌĆō`PI-03`: Content section for Box with Text children.
- `PF-01`ŌĆō`PF-16` (in `panel-form.spec.ts`): Input, Textarea, Checkbox, Toggle.
- `PD-01`ŌĆō`PD-11` (in `panel-display.spec.ts`): Heading, Badge, Avatar.
- `PM-01`ŌĆō`PM-10` (in `panel-media.spec.ts`): Image (placeholder, resize, src), Icon (size/color), Icon Tap.
- `T1`ŌĆō`T11`: Dimension, rotate, NumberInput, moveNode, drop zone, opacity.
- `U1`ŌĆō`U14`: Alignment, flip, auto layout, gap, clip, stroke, typography, DOM visual update.
- `V1`ŌĆō`V8`: Color pickers, visibility with gap, section visibility per node type, self-alignment.
- `DI-01`ŌĆō`DI-04`: Drop indicator direction ŌĆö vertical line for row/HStack, horizontal for column.
- `Fix-DropLine-1/2`: Drop line not shown over dragged node, moveNode correct index placement.

**Selection in E2E ŌĆö use Layers panel, not canvas click:**
Canvas click-to-select can be unreliable in Playwright/headless ŌĆö the capture overlay's `onPointerDown` may not fire. For tests that need a node selected, use the Layers panel instead:
```ts
await page.getByTestId('tab-layers').click();
await page.getByTestId('layer-row').first().click();
```

**Injected nodes must have `id` fields:** Without `id`, the renderer does not set `data-builder-id`, making `waitForSelector('[data-builder-id="..."]')` time out.

**Timeout:** Global Playwright timeout is `30_000`ms (fail fast). The dev server must be running on port 3001 (`npx next dev -p 3001`). The `webServer` startup timeout is `60_000`ms. Workers are set to `10` (matching CPU count) so all 12 spec files run simultaneously.

