### 15. Resize handles float over the drag ghost

**Root cause:** `BuilderOverlay` was not aware that a drag was in progress, so it kept rendering selection rings and resize handles on top of the ghost image.

**Fix:** Added `isDragging: boolean` state to `_canvas.tsx` ŌĆö set to `true` inside the `requestAnimationFrame` of `onDragStart`, cleared in both `onDrop` and `onDragEnd`. Pass `isDragging` as a prop to `BuilderOverlay`. In the overlay, gate the hover outline, single-selection ring, resize handles, multi-select highlights, crosshairs, and dimension tooltip behind `!isDragging`.

**Rule:** Any new overlay element that would look wrong while dragging (e.g. labels, handles, distance lines) must also be gated with `!isDragging`.

