### 16. Multi-select drag: clicking a selected node deselects others before drag starts

**Root cause:** The capture overlay's `onPointerDown` called `select(hit.id, e.shiftKey)` unconditionally. Without shift, this replaced the entire multi-selection with just the clicked node ŌĆö so by the time `onDragStart` fired, `selectedIds` only ever had one entry.

**Fix:** Guard in `onPointerDown`:
```tsx
if (hit.kind === 'node') {
  const { selectedIds: curIds } = useBuilderStore.getState();
  // Only change selection if the node isn't already selected (or shift is held).
  // Preserve multi-selection for drag; onPointerUp reduces it if no drag occurred.
  if (!curIds.includes(hit.id) || e.shiftKey) {
    select(hit.id, e.shiftKey);
  }
}
```
`onPointerUp` already handles reducing multi-selection to single on a plain click with no drag.

**Rule:** `onPointerDown` on the capture overlay must NEVER replace an existing multi-selection when the clicked node is already selected without shift ŌĆö doing so destroys multi-select drag before it starts.

