## ┬¦29 Context-Dependent Sub-Component Crash Guard ŌĆö REQUIRED_PARENT + ALLOWED_CHILDREN

**Root cause:** Gluestack sub-components like `CheckboxIndicator`, etc. use `useStyleContext(SCOPE)` to read styling from their parent. Moving them outside their required parent makes that context `undefined` ŌåÆ hard crash.

**Fix:** `moveNode` in `_store.ts` validates both directions before any tree mutation:
```typescript
// Node requires a specific parent type
const REQUIRED_PARENT: Record<string, string> = { CheckboxIndicator: 'Checkbox' /* ... */ };
if (REQUIRED_PARENT[node.type]) {
  const newParent = newParentId ? findNode(s.pageNodes, newParentId) : null;
  if (!newParent || newParent.type !== REQUIRED_PARENT[node.type]) return s;
}
// Parent only accepts specific child types
const ALLOWED: Record<string, Set<string>> = { Checkbox: new Set(['CheckboxIndicator', 'CheckboxLabel']) };
if (newParentId) {
  const newParent = findNode(s.pageNodes, newParentId);
  if (newParent && ALLOWED[newParent.type] && !ALLOWED[newParent.type].has(node.type)) return s;
}
```

**Rule:** Any time you add a Gluestack compound component that uses `useStyleContext`, add it to `REQUIRED_PARENT` and the parent type to `ALLOWED` in `_store.ts`.

