## ┬¦30 Layers Panel ŌĆö Drag-to-Reorder + Drop-into-Empty-Container

**Features implemented:**
- Every `LayerRow` has `draggable` and full HTML5 DnD handlers (`onDragStart`, `onDragOver`, `onDrop`, `onDragEnd`).
- `LayerDragState` tracks `{ dragId, dropTargetId, dropPosition: 'above' | 'inside' | 'below' }`.
- Container rows use **thirds**: top 33% = above (blue top border), middle 34% = inside (blue outline), bottom 33% = below (blue bottom border). Non-container rows use top/bottom halves only.
- `handleLayerDrop` handles all three positions:
  - `'above'` / `'below'` ŌåÆ insert at `targetIdx` / `targetIdx + 1` in target's parent
  - `'inside'` ŌåÆ `moveNode(dragId, dropTargetId, childCount)` ŌĆö works even when the container has zero children
- Chevron icon size increased from 8px ŌåÆ 13px.

**Click-to-deselect:** The scrollable tree wrapper (`data-testid="layers-tree"`) has an `onClick` that calls `store.select(null)` when the click doesn't land on any `[data-layer-row]` element. Every `LayerRow` root `div` has `data-layer-row` to enable this check.

**Multi-select in layers:** When `dragId` is in the current `selectedIds` AND `selectedIds.length > 1`, `handleLayerDrop` calls `moveNodes(selectedIds, ...)` instead of `moveNode`.

**Rule:** `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` (same set as `CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_canvas.tsx`) drives the thirds/halves decision. Keep it in sync when adding new container types.

