## ┬¦35 Formula Binding ŌĆö `FieldWithBinding`, `ToggleBind`, and Class-Based Fields

### FieldWithBinding ŌĆö Two Layout Modes

`FieldWithBinding` in `_formula-panel.tsx` wraps any input with a bind icon (Ōēł). When a formula is applied the input is replaced by "ŲÆ Edit formula".

- **Default layout** (no `stackLayout`): children + Ōēł side-by-side. Use for number/text inputs where the bind icon can sit to the right.
- **Stack layout** (`stackLayout`): displayLabel + Ōēł on top row, children or "ŲÆ Edit formula" below. Use when children are wide (toggle button groups, 9-cell grids, direction buttons) to prevent horizontal overflow.

**Rule:** Never put `FieldWithBinding` (which has `flex: 1`) inside a header row (`justifyContent: space-between`) alongside a `SectionHeader`. The FieldWithBinding expands and the "ŲÆ Edit formula" button inflates the header when bound. Instead:
1. Place `SectionHeader` alone at the top.
2. Place `FieldWithBinding` with `stackLayout` below it, with the interactive controls as its children.

```tsx
// ŌØī BAD ŌĆö FieldWithBinding in header row inflates it when bound
<div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between' }}>
  <SectionHeader title="Self Alignment" />
  <FieldWithBinding label="selfAlignment" ...><span /></FieldWithBinding>
</div>
{!isBound && <div>toggles</div>}

// Ō£ģ GOOD ŌĆö SectionHeader alone, FieldWithBinding wraps toggles with stackLayout
<SectionHeader title="Self Alignment" />
<FieldWithBinding label="selfAlignment" stackLayout ...>
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: 4 }}>{toggles}</div>
</FieldWithBinding>
```

This applies to: **Self Alignment**, **Alignment** (9-cell grid), **Auto Layout** (direction buttons).

