## ┬¦40 Form System ŌĆö Builder Architecture

### Overview

The form system has two layers:

1. **Runtime** ŌĆö `FormContainer` component + `ControlledInputField` auto-tracking via `FormContext` in `lib/sdui/components/`. Field values are written by `ControlledInputField.handleChange ŌåÆ formCtx.setField(name, value)`. To pre-populate fields programmatically, use `setVar` with `path: "local.data.form.formData.fieldName"`.
2. **Builder** ŌĆö Settings tab in `_panel-right.tsx` that configures per-field properties stored as `_`-prefixed node fields

### Node-level form fields (underscore prefix)

These fields live on the `SDUINode` (not in `props`) and are only meaningful at build/config time:

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `node.name` | `string` | Human label AND the `name` prop value used for `ControlledInputField` auto-tracking |
| `node._initialValue` | `unknown` | Seed value passed to `FormContainer.props.initialFormData[field]` |
| `node._debounce` | `{ delay: number, minLength?: number }` | Stored on the node; runtime debounce is handled by `ControlledInputField` |
| `node._validation.rules` | `ValidationRule[]` | Array of rules run on change / submit |
| `node._forceDisabledInEditor` | `boolean` | When `disabled` is formula-bound, force the overlay to show in the builder |
| `node._disabledOverlay` | `{ color?, opacity?, blur? }` | Visual overlay rendered when disabled |
| `node._forceShowInEditor` | `boolean` | When `condition` hides the node, force it visible in the builder |

**Rule:** Never store these as `props.*` keys ŌĆö they are builder metadata, not runtime props.

### `SDUINode` type additions

```ts
// lib/sdui/types/node.ts
export interface SDUINode {
  // ...existing fields...
  name?: string;
  _initialValue?: unknown;
  _debounce?: { delay: number; minLength?: number };
  _disabledOverlay?: { color?: string; opacity?: number; blur?: number };
  _forceDisabledInEditor?: boolean;
  _forceShowInEditor?: boolean;
}
```

