## ┬¦46 Form System ŌĆö `patchNodeFieldLive` vs `patchNodeField`

Two store methods exist for patching a node field:

| Method | History | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `patchNodeField(id, field, value)` | Yes ŌĆö calls `_pushHistory` | Discrete changes (checkbox toggle, dropdown select, text commit on blur) |
| `patchNodeFieldLive(id, field, value)` | No | Continuous drag/slide updates (slider drag, color picker circle) |

**Rule:** When building any panel control that involves continuous user gestures (range slider, drag handle, color picker), always use `patchNodeFieldLive` for the onChange handler and call `store._pushHistory()` once in `onMouseUp` / `onBlur` / `onCommit`.

This prevents:
1. **History flooding** ŌĆö undo jumps only milliseconds back instead of to the state before the gesture
2. **Performance jank** ŌĆö `_pushHistory` does a full deep-clone of the page node tree; calling it 60x/sec causes visible lag

