## ┬¦42 Form Workflow Step Types ŌĆö Builder Rules

### Overview

Two workflow step types are form-specific and only appear in the action-type picker when `isFormContext` is true (i.e. the selected element **is** a `FormContainer` or any descendant of one). They appear under the **"Other"** category in `FORM_ACTION_CATEGORY` inside `_workflow-canvas.tsx`.

| Step type | Label | Config |
|---|---|---|
| `setFormState` | Set form state | `isSubmitting` (bool/formula), `isSubmitted` (bool/formula) |
| `resetForm` | Reset form | No config ŌĆö resets all fields to initial values |

### `FORM_ACTION_CATEGORY` category label

The category label is **`"Other"`** (not `"Form"`) to match the reference design. Do not change this label.

### `FormContainer` element triggers

`ELEMENT_TRIGGERS['FormContainer']` defines two triggers that appear at the top of the trigger dropdown when the selected element is a `FormContainer`:

```ts
FormContainer: [
  { value: 'submit',                label: 'On submit' },
  { value: 'submitValidationError', label: 'On submit validation error' },
],
```

### Inline actions ŌĆö hidden from Workflows tab

The Workflows tab only shows user-created named workflow references (`{ action: "uuid" }`). Any entry in the legacy `rawActionsObj` format whose `actionDef` has a `type` property is an inline system action and is filtered out:

```ts
workflowEntries = Object.entries(rawActionsObj)
  .filter(([, actionDef]) => !(actionDef as any)?.type)  // skip inline action objects
  .map(...)
```

**Note:** The builder no longer auto-injects any inline actions when a node is dropped inside a `FormContainer`. Field tracking is purely via `node.props.name`.

### `isFormContext` detection

`isFormContext` is computed in `WorkflowCanvas` using `hasFormContainerAncestor(pageNodes, targetNodeId)` from `_store.ts`. It is passed to `NodePropsPanel` and `TypeSearchDropdown` to conditionally inject `FORM_ACTION_CATEGORY` into the picker.

