## ┬¦55 Formula Editor ŌĆö Workflow Chip Labels (liveCanvasSteps)

### Problem: Static "Action N" chip numbers

When a workflow action was added before an existing step (shifting its position), or when an action was renamed in the canvas, formula chips built from that step's result continued to show the old "Action N" number or the old cached name ŌĆö they never updated.

**Root cause:** The chip label was derived from `currentWorkflowTestResults` ŌĆö the last-saved test run. That data is frozen at run time and does not change as the canvas is edited.

### Fix: `staticStepMap` from `liveCanvasSteps`

`_formula-editor.tsx` now derives chip labels from `liveCanvasSteps` (the live in-editor step list, updated on every canvas edit):

```ts
// staticStepMap: stepId ŌåÆ { pos: 1-based index, name?: user-defined name }
const staticStepMap = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map<string, { pos: number; name?: string }>();
  (liveCanvasSteps ?? []).forEach((step, i) => {
    map.set(step.id, { pos: i + 1, name: step.name || undefined });
  });
  return map;
}, [liveCanvasSteps]);

// stepNameMap: stepId ŌåÆ human-readable display label (used by chips + Workflow tab header)
const stepNameMap = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map<string, string>();
  // Priority 1: live canvas name or index (always wins)
  for (const [id, { pos, name }] of staticStepMap) {
    map.set(id, name ?? `Action ${pos}`);
  }
  // Priority 2: cached actionName from test results (only for steps no longer in canvas)
  for (const [stepId, entry] of Object.entries(currentWorkflowTestResults ?? {})) {
    if (!map.has(stepId) && entry.actionName) map.set(stepId, entry.actionName);
  }
  return map;
}, [staticStepMap, currentWorkflowTestResults]);
```

**Priority order:**
1. User-defined `name` from live canvas (`step.name`)
2. `"Action N"` using live position (`pos`)
3. Cached `entry.actionName` from test results ŌĆö **only** when the step is no longer in the canvas

This ensures:
- Adding steps before an existing one immediately updates that step's chip number
- Naming a step shows the name in chips immediately (no need to re-run)
- Removing a name reverts to "Action N" instantly (no stale cache)
- The "FROM ACTION" header in the Workflow tab reflects live canvas names

### Pasted formula chips

When a formula is pasted into the editor, `insertPastedFormulaAtCaret` calls `populateEditor` which converts `context.workflow['stepId'].*` paths to chips. The `stepNameMap` must be passed through so pasted chips also show human-readable labels instead of raw step IDs.

```ts
// _formula-editor-dom.ts
export function insertPastedFormulaAtCaret(
  editorEl: HTMLElement,
  text: string,
  dsMap: Map<string, { label: string }>,
  varMap?: Map<string, { label: string }>,
  stepNameMap?: Map<string, string>, // ŌåÉ required for correct chip labels on paste
): void { ... }
```

### Label reactivity useEffect

After `stepNameMap` changes, existing chips in the DOM (already rendered) must also update their displayed label. A `useEffect` rescans all `[data-type="collection"],[data-type="error"]` chips in the editor, filters to those whose `data-formula` starts with `context.workflow['`, and updates their visible text:

```ts
useEffect(() => {
  const editorEl = editorRef.current;
  if (!editorEl) return;
  editorEl.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-type="collection"],[data-type="error"]')
    .forEach(chip => {
      const formulaPath = chip.dataset.formula ?? '';
      if (!formulaPath.startsWith("context.workflow['")) return;
      const stepIdMatch = formulaPath.match(/^context\.workflow\['([^']*)'\]/);
      const stepId = stepIdMatch?.[1];
      if (!stepId) return;
      const label = stepNameMap.get(stepId);
      if (label) { /* update chip's inner text node */ }
    });
}, [stepNameMap]);
```

**Rule:** Use the attribute selector `[data-type="collection"],[data-type="error"]` and filter in JavaScript ŌĆö do NOT use `[data-formula^="context.workflow['"]` in CSS (special characters make it unreliable in some browsers).

