## ┬¦56 Formula Editor ŌĆö `local?.data` Optional Chaining in CHIP_RE

### Problem

`CHIP_RE` only matched `local.data` (no optional chaining prefix). Formulas stored as `local?.data?.form?.formData?.['fieldName']` were not tokenized into chips ŌĆö the entire expression fell through as plain text.

### Fix

`CHIP_RE` was updated to accept `local?.data` and optional-chaining path segments:

```
// Before: only dot notation
local\.data(?:\?\.\['[^']*'\]|\?\.\[\d+\]|\.[\w$]+)*

// After: optional ? before .data, and ?.word segments
local\??\.data(?:\??\.(?:\['[^']*'\]|[\w$]+)|\?\.\[\d+\])*
```

This matches all of:
- `local.data` ŌĆö original canonical form
- `local?.data` ŌĆö optional-chaining prefix
- `local.data.form.field` ŌĆö dot notation segments
- `local?.data?.form?.formData?.['fieldName']` ŌĆö full optional-chaining form

`populateEditor` was also updated to use a robust segment-by-segment parser for both `local.data` and `local?.data` paths:

```ts
} else if (/^local\??\.data/.test(formulaPath)) {
  const stripped = formulaPath.replace(/^local\??\.data/, '');
  const segs: Array<string | number> = [];
  let rem = stripped;
  while (rem.length > 0) {
    const bracketM = rem.match(/^\??\.(?:\['([^']+)'\])(.*)/s);
    if (bracketM) { segs.push(bracketM[1]); rem = bracketM[2]; continue; }
    const numM = rem.match(/^\?\.\[(\d+)\](.*)/s);
    if (numM) { segs.push(Number(numM[1])); rem = numM[2]; continue; }
    const wordM = rem.match(/^\??\.(\w[\w$]*)(.*)/s);
    if (wordM) { segs.push(wordM[1]); rem = wordM[2]; continue; }
    break;
  }
  const normalized = 'local.data' + segs.map(s =>
    typeof s === 'number' ? `?.[${s}]` : `?.['${s}']`
  ).join('');
  const friendly = 'local.data' + segs.map(s =>
    typeof s === 'number' ? `[${s}]` : `.${s}`
  ).join('');
  el.appendChild(buildChipSpan(normalized, friendly, 'form'));
}
```

**Rule:** All `local.data.*` and `local?.data.*` paths render as green `form` chips. The canonical storage form is `local.data?.['seg']` (no `?` before `.data`); the parser accepts both forms when reading back from JSON.

